Program: Great Lives
Title: James Gillray
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b0076brj
Last Broadcast Date: Fri 28 Nov 2014
Political cartoonist Steve Bell chooses the 18th century caricaturist James Gillray. With Sheila O'Connell, curator of prints and drawings at British Museum and actor James Bolam. Presented by Humphrey Carpenter. The biographical series in which a distinguished guest chooses someone who's inspired their life. Will their hero stand up to intensive scrutiny and merit the description of having led a great life? From 2002. Show less